CEO The Work Lagoon & Country Manager Teamtailor

Helsinki Area, Finland • Staffing and Recruiting • 500 connections

Summary

My great interest in people and MBA grade from Aalto Executive Education program encouraged me to start my own business. During my 25 years in working life, I have seen so many great individuals: managers, entrepreneurs and ordinary employees - that have had huge potential but lacking the support or breeding ground to develop and perform at their full potential.

What can be done to make sure companies have the best and most suitable persons working with tasks that they enjoy and where the can use all their potential? What can companies do to support talents and make sure they remain in the company and do not run to a competitor?

Most companies can do a lot to develop a stronger Employer Brand and build talent management programs. These are among key factors for successful companies, together with general well-being programs.

I want to partner with young companies, their founders and managers, and support them in HR-related issues from the very beginning.

I have a wide knowledge of health-care and social work. I took an exam in practical nursing simultaneously with my MBA. This unique combination of the two exams and my earlier work experience from the sector makes me a true expert in staff support like mentoring, developing motivation tools and career building and employer branding in a sector where very little is done so far.

Applying positive psychology with its newest research and person-centred practises employers can make the difference with their competitors. This can be the difference that attract talented employees and make everyone perform better and at the end the company can save in personal costs. I believe that employees with a clear sense of purpose, and whose roles are decided based on strengths and interests give the most. A person-centered team knows what is important to individuals themselves and for its members.

Entrepreneur, CEO, The Work Lagoon Ltd
Sep 2015 - current

In today’s business world employees are more important than ever before. To be successful companies have to understand humans and fulfil their needs differently than before. Finding the purpose and motivational factors raises the level of performance, both for teams and individuals. Successful companies bring HR into their strategy and partner recruiters and marketers to work for the same brand values. Employees are as important as customers. The Work Lagoon as a HR partner supports your leadership teams by implementing HR to the company strategy. Employer Branding and Talent Management are comparable to product and service development and branding, they cannot be neglected in the global job market. Employer Branding surveys are valued measurements of company reputations. They tell if the expectations meet the reality. We use WorkPlace Big 5 personality assessment to help employers to recruit the most suitable persons, to choose right people to become managers, to build optimal teams etc. The test is extremely reliable in comparison to other available personality assessments, well-accepted by those taking the assessment and it is focused on behaviors in the work environment. We implement the theories of positive psychology and person-centred practises to raise the level of well-being and performance. We believe that colleagues working in person-centred organisations are more motivated, better communicators, give better support and are better equipped to understand and implement change.
